Definition: having or showing a sense of what is fitting and considerate in dealing with others
Example: she was tactful enough not to shatter his illusion; a tactful remark eased her embarrassment
Synonyms: noun, attribute, tactfulness, TACTLESS, CONSIDERATE, having, or, showing, a, sense, of, what, is, fitting, and, considerate, in, dealing, with, others, she, was, tactful, enough, not, to, shatter, his, illusion, remark, eased, her, embarrassment
Category: adj.all
